The RDI I is built around a central linking spine.

102
00:04:40.955 --> 00:04:42.645
It's a list that aims to estimate every,

103
00:04:42.745 --> 00:04:44.565
the ever resident population of New Zealand.

104
00:04:44.745 --> 00:04:47.285
So every person who's ever been here is a resident,

105
00:04:47.345 --> 00:04:50.805
and it's made by combining tax, birth and migration records.

106
00:04:52.145 --> 00:04:55.245
Making the data accessible while keeping it safe is an

